# Coding Conventions

## Backend (NestJS)

### Module Pattern

Every feature module follows this structure:
```
modules/feature-name/
  feature-name.module.ts       # @Module with imports, controllers, providers, exports
  feature-name.controller.ts   # HTTP routes, @UseGuards, @Roles
  feature-name.service.ts      # Business logic, Repository injection
  dto/
    create-feature.dto.ts      # class-validator decorators
    update-feature.dto.ts
```

### Entity Conventions

- File: `src/entities/feature-name.entity.ts`
- Export from `src/entities/index.ts`
- Register in `app.module.ts` TypeOrmModule entities array
- Primary key: `@PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')` named `feature_name_id`
- Timestamps: `@CreateDateColumn({ name: 'create_at' })` or `created_at`
- Enums: define in entity file, export alongside entity
- Relations: always specify `onDelete` behavior

```typescript
@Entity('table_name')
export class FeatureName {
  @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')
  feature_name_id: string;

  @Column({ type: 'varchar', length: 255 })
  name: string;

  @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at' })
  created_at: Date;

  @ManyToOne(() => Parent, (p) => p.children, { onDelete: 'CASCADE' })
  @JoinColumn({ name: 'parent_id' })
  parent: Parent;
}
```

### DTO Conventions

- Use `class-validator` decorators: `@IsString()`, `@IsUUID()`, `@IsOptional()`, `@IsEnum()`
- Use `class-transformer` if needed
- Extend `PartialType(CreateDto)` for update DTOs

### Error Handling

- Use `AppException(ErrorCode, message, HttpStatus)` from `common/errors`
- Add new error codes to `ErrorCode` enum in `common/errors/error-codes.ts`
- Global `GlobalExceptionFilter` shapes all HTTP errors

### Service Pattern

- Inject repositories via `@InjectRepository(Entity)`
- Use `QueryBuilder` for complex queries, `.find()` for simple ones
- Always validate existence before operations (throw `AppException` if not found)
- Logger: `private readonly logger = new Logger(ServiceName.name)`

### Migration

- Generate: `npm run migration:generate src/migrations/TIMESTAMP-Description`
- Run: `npm run migration:run`
- Revert: `npm run migration:revert`
- Never use `synchronize: true` in production

### Auth Guards

- `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard)` + `@Roles(UserRole.ADMIN)` on controller
- `@Public()` decorator to skip auth on specific routes
- `@CurrentUser()` decorator to get authenticated user

## Frontend (Next.js)

### Page Pattern (App Router)

- Server Components by default, `'use client'` only when needed
- Route params in Next.js 16: `params` is a `Promise`, unwrap with `use()`
- Layout wraps children, pages are leaf components

### Component Conventions

- Functional components only
- Props interface above component
- Use `cn()` from `lib/cn.ts` for conditional classNames
- Tailwind CSS classes inline, no CSS modules

### Hook Conventions

- Custom hooks in `hooks/` directory
- Use TanStack Query for server state: `useQuery`, `useInfiniteQuery`, `useMutation`
- Query keys: `['resource', identifier]` pattern
- Use Zustand for client state (stores/)

### API Calls

- Use `api` instance from `lib/axios.ts` (auto-attaches Bearer token)
- REST calls via `api.get()`, `api.post()`, etc.
- Socket events via `useSocket()` hook

### State Management

- **Zustand** for client state (auth token, UI state like active room, filters)
- **React Query** for server state (rooms, messages, shops)
- Never duplicate server state in Zustand

### Form Handling

- `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers/zod`
- Schemas in `schemas/` directory using `zod`
